	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Lagos - Boko Haram Islamists who kidnapped more than 100 schoolgirls in Dapchi, northeast Nigeria, just over a month ago have returned the students to the town, two parents told AFP on Wednesday. "The girls have been brought back. They were brought in nine vehicles and dropped outside the school at about 08:00 ," said Bashir Manzo, who heads a group set up to support parents whose children were abducted. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  